Bring a large pan of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the noodles. Trim the
@green beans{80%g} then chop in half. Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Peel
and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the
@lime{1}(zested and cut into wedges) and cut into wedges. Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g}
in a #sieve{}.

When the saucepan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook until
tender, ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a sieve.

While the noodles are cooking, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large
#frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir fry for
~{2%minutes}.

Add the @king prawns{150%g} and sweetcorn and continue stir frying for
~{3-4%minutes}, until the beans are tender and the prawns are just cooked. Add the
garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the @Pad Thai paste{50%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, half the lime zest and the noodles
to the pan and mix well. Add a splash of @water{1%splash} to loosen if you need to.
Cook until the noodles are piping hot.

Divide the pad thai between plates and top with the spring onion, remaining lime zest
and lime wedges. Enjoy!